TY  - JOUR
TI  - Price Elasticities for Local Telephone Calls
AU  - Park, Rolla Edward
AU  - Wetzel, Bruce M.
AU  - Mitchell, Bridger M.
AB  - [Price elasticities are estimated for local telephone calls and minutes of conversation using data from a pricing experiment in central Illinois conducted by General Telephone and Electronics. The experiment charges separately for calls and for minutes. Using a model that is consistent with the theory of telephone demand, the authors estimate the effects of both prices. The nonlinear generalized least squares estimates of the elasticities are fairly small--about 0.1 or less in absolute value at experimental price levels--but they are estimated with high precision. The report briefly considers the application of these results to predict the effects of introducing measured service telephone rates in other cities.]
